00:33:53.120 --> 00:33:56.670
Well, maybe I'll just
carry it out.

00:33:56.670 --> 00:33:58.510
Because that's always nice.

00:33:58.510 --> 00:34:03.630
So we have 1 + x ^2
/ a ^2 - x ^2.

00:34:03.630 --> 00:34:07.060
That's 1 + (y ') ^2.

00:34:07.060 --> 00:34:09.630
And now I put this over
a common denominator.

00:34:09.630 --> 00:34:11.800
And I get a ^2 - x ^2.

00:34:11.800 --> 00:34:15.030
And I have in the numerator
a ^2 - x ^2 + x^2.

00:34:15.030 --> 00:34:17.590
So the same cancellation
occurs.

00:34:17.590 --> 00:34:25.390
But now we get an a ^2
in the numerator.

00:34:25.390 --> 00:34:28.070
So now I can set up the ds.

00:34:28.070 --> 00:34:30.200
And so here's what happens.

00:34:30.200 --> 00:34:35.370
The area of a section of the
sphere, so let's see.

00:34:35.370 --> 00:34:39.270
We're going to start at some
starting place x1, and end at

00:34:39.270 --> 00:34:40.760
some place x2.

00:34:40.760 --> 00:34:43.110
So what does that look like?

00:34:43.110 --> 00:34:45.140
Here's the sphere.

00:34:45.140 --> 00:34:47.490
And we're starting
at a place x1.

00:34:47.490 --> 00:34:49.810
And we're ending
at a place x2.

00:34:49.810 --> 00:34:53.830
And we're taking more or less
the slice here, if you like.

00:34:53.830 --> 00:34:59.480
The section of this sphere.

00:34:59.480 --> 00:35:02.150
So the area's going
to equal this.

00:35:02.150 --> 00:35:06.730
And what is it going to be?

00:35:06.730 --> 00:35:12.820
Well, so I have here 2 pi y.

00:35:12.820 --> 00:35:15.310
I'll write it out, just
leave it as y for now.

00:35:15.310 --> 00:35:19.190
And then I have ds.

00:35:19.190 --> 00:35:22.110
So that's always what the
formula is when you're

00:35:22.110 --> 00:35:25.880
revolving around the x axis.

00:35:25.880 --> 00:35:29.920
And then I'll plug in
for those things.

00:35:29.920 --> 00:35:38.700
So 2 pi, the formula for y is
square root a ^2 - x ^2.

00:35:38.700 --> 00:35:42.860
And the formula for ds, well,
it's the square root

00:35:42.860 --> 00:35:44.970
of this times dx.

00:35:44.970 --> 00:35:51.760
So it's the square root of
a ^2 / a ^2 - x ^2 dx.

00:35:51.760 --> 00:35:54.880
So this part is ds.

00:35:54.880 --> 00:36:02.170
And this part is y.

00:36:02.170 --> 00:36:05.230
And now, I claim we have a nice

00:36:05.230 --> 00:36:07.590
cancellation that takes place.

00:36:07.590 --> 00:36:09.770
Square root of a ^2 = a.

00:36:09.770 --> 00:36:12.740
And then there's another
good cancellation.

00:36:12.740 --> 00:36:13.990
As you can see.

00:36:13.990 --> 00:36:17.805
Now, what we get here is the
integral from x1 to x2, of 2

00:36:17.805 --> 00:36:21.160
pi a dx, which is about
the easiest

00:36:21.160 --> 00:36:23.340
integral you can imagine.

00:36:23.340 --> 00:36:24.940
It's just the integral
of a constant.

00:36:24.940 --> 00:36:36.810
So it's 2 pi a ( x2 - x1).

00:36:36.810 --> 00:36:40.780
Let's check this in a
couple of examples.

00:36:40.780 --> 00:36:48.390
And then see what it's saying
geometrically, a little bit.

00:36:48.390 --> 00:36:54.190
So what this is saying, so
special cases that you should

00:36:54.190 --> 00:36:58.220
always check when you have a
nice formula like this, at

00:36:58.220 --> 00:37:01.250
least. But really with anything
in order to make sure

00:37:01.250 --> 00:37:03.250
that you've got the
right answer.

00:37:03.250 --> 00:37:05.710
If you take, for example,
the hemisphere.

00:37:05.710 --> 00:37:08.920
So you take 1/2 of
this sphere.

00:37:08.920 --> 00:37:11.090
So that would be starting
at 0, sorry.

00:37:11.090 --> 00:37:14.300
And ending at a.

00:37:14.300 --> 00:37:17.270
So that's the integral
from 0 to a.

00:37:17.270 --> 00:37:21.890
So this is the case
x1 = 0. x2 = a.

00:37:21.890 --> 00:37:29.190
And what you're going to
get is a hemisphere.

00:37:29.190 --> 00:37:36.270
And the area is (2 pi a ) a.

00:37:36.270 --> 00:37:42.410
Or in other words, 2 pi a ^2.

00:37:42.410 --> 00:37:50.520
And if you take the whole
sphere, that's starting at x1

00:37:50.520 --> 00:38:02.640
= - a, and x2 = a, you're
getting (2 pi a) ( a - (- a)).

00:38:02.640 --> 00:38:06.380
Which is 4 pi a ^2.

00:38:06.380 --> 00:38:09.230
That's the whole thing.

00:38:09.230 --> 00:38:10.140
Yeah, question.

00:38:10.140 --> 00:38:21.780
STUDENT: [INAUDIBLE]

00:38:21.780 --> 00:38:24.590
PROFESSOR: The question is,
